<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-12-04T15:51:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-12-04T15:51:00-05:00" n="49" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d49">
                        <head>49. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss>
                            to the <gloss type="to">Mission at the United Nations</gloss><note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d49fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                                Files, 320.11/12–458. Confidential. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_BWB1">Buffum</persName>, cleared by <persName corresp="#p_NWT1">Nunley</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BRE3">Bacon</persName>, and approved by <persName corresp="#p_CWI1">Cargo</persName> who signed for
                            Herter.</note></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1958-12-04T15:51:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December 4,
                                        1958—3:51 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><gloss target="#t_GADEL1">Gadel</gloss> 162. In view status Hungarian
                            Credentials problem, <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> should
                            urgently seek postponement meeting Credentials Committee until after
                            plenary consideration Hungarian item.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="strong">Herter</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>